df-har
blocks.content: Define the _Hartogs function_ , which maps all sets to the smallest ordinal that cannot be injected into the given set. In the important special case where ` x ` is an ordinal, this is the _cardinal successor_ operation. Traditionally, the Hartogs number of a set is written ` aleph ( X ) ` and the cardinal successor ` X + ` ; we use functional notation for this, and cannot use the aleph symbol because it is taken for the enumerating function of the infinite initial ordinals ~ df-aleph . Some authors define the Hartogs number of a set to be the least *infinite* ordinal which does not inject into it, thus causing the range to consist only of alephs. We use the simpler definition where the value can be any successor cardinal. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 11-Feb-2015.)

blocks.name: df-wdom
blocks.content: A set is _weakly dominated_ by a "larger" set iff the "larger" set can be mapped onto the "smaller" set or the smaller set is empty; equivalently if the smaller set can be placed into bijection with some partition of the larger set. When choice is assumed (as ~ fodom ), this coincides with the 1-1 definition ~ df-dom ; however, it is not known whether this is a choice-equivalent or a strictly weaker form. Some discussion of this question can be found at ~ http://boolesrings.org/asafk/2014/on-the-partition-principle/ . (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 11-Feb-2015.)

  reldom()
  brwdom(hs0, c1, universe, c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
}

blocks.name: wdomtr
blocks.content: Transitivity of weak dominance. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 11-Feb-2015.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 5-May-2015.)
blocks.origin:
thm wdomtr(class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  |- wi(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
} = {
  pm2.61dne(c0, emptycls, wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  syl(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wi(wceq(c0, emptycls), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2)), wcel(c2, universe))
  adantl(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wcel(c2, universe))
  brrelex2i(c1, cwdom, c2)
  relwdom()
  syl5ibrcom(wcel(c2, universe), wceq(c0, emptycls), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wbr(emptycls, cwdom, c2))
  0wdom(c2, universe)
  breq1(c0, emptycls, cwdom, c2)
  ex(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  exlimddv(hs0, wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  mpbid(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wex(hs0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c1))
  simpll(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wne(c0, emptycls))
  adantl(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls), wb(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wex(hs0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))))
  brwdomn0(hs0, c0, c1)
  mpd(wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wex(hs1, wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1)))
  mpbid(wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wex(hs1, wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1)), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2))
  simpllr(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wne(c0, emptycls), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  syl(wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wb(wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wex(hs1, wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1))), wne(c1, emptycls))
  mpbid(wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wne(c1, emptycls), wne(c0, emptycls))
  simplr(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  adantl(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wb(wne(c0, emptycls), wne(c1, emptycls)))
  3bitr3rd(wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wne(c0, emptycls), wne(c1, emptycls), wne(cdm(cv(hs0)), emptycls), wne(crn(cv(hs0)), emptycls))
  a1i(wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wb(wne(cdm(cv(hs0)), emptycls), wne(crn(cv(hs0)), emptycls)))
  necon3bii(cdm(cv(hs0)), emptycls, crn(cv(hs0)), emptycls)
  dm0rn0(cv(hs0))
  neeq1d(cdm(cv(hs0)), emptycls, c1, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  fdmd(cv(hs0), c1, c0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  fof(cv(hs0), c1, c0)
  neeq1d(crn(cv(hs0)), emptycls, c0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0))
  forn(cv(hs0), c1, c0)
  brwdomn0(hs1, c1, c2)
  exlimdv(hs1, wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)), wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  expr(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  adantl(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wa(wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  sylancr(wa(wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wfo(cv(hs1), c2, c1)), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wcel(ccom(cv(hs0), cv(hs1)), universe), wfo(ccom(cv(hs0), cv(hs1)), c2, c0))
  coex(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))
  vex(hs0)
  vex(hs1)
  foco(cv(hs0), c1, c0, cv(hs1), c2)
  fowdom(ccom(cv(hs0), cv(hs1)), universe, c2, c0)
  diff.hs0.w(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)))
  diff.hs0.w(wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs1.c(c1)
  diff.hs1.c(c2)
  diff.hs1.w(wa(wa(wa(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)), wne(c0, emptycls)), wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)))
  diff.hs1.w(wbr(c0, cwdom, c2))
}

  simpllr(c0[‚âº*]c1, c1[‚âº*]c2, c0 ‚â† ‚àÖ, (hs0 : c1 ‚Ü† c0))
  syl((((c0[‚âº*]c1 ‚àß c1[‚âº*]c2)‚àß c0 ‚â† ‚àÖ)‚àß(hs0 : c1 ‚Ü† c0)), (c1[‚âº*]c2 ‚Üî ‚àÉ(hs1,(hs1 : c2 ‚Ü† c1))), c1 ‚â† ‚àÖ)
  mpbid((((c0[‚âº*]c1 ‚àß c1[‚âº*]c2)‚àß c0 ‚â† ‚àÖ)‚àß(hs0 : c1 ‚Ü† c0)), c1 ‚â† ‚àÖ, c0 ‚â† ‚àÖ)

  3bitr3rd((hs0 : c1 ‚Ü† c0), c0 ‚â† ‚àÖ, c1 ‚â† ‚àÖ, dom(hs0)‚â† ‚àÖ, ran(hs0)‚â† ‚àÖ)
  a1i((hs0 : c1 ‚Ü† c0), (dom(hs0)‚â† ‚àÖ ‚Üî ran(hs0)‚â† ‚àÖ))

blocks.content: Equality-like theorem for equinumerosity and weak dominance. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 18-May-2015.)

thm wdomen1(class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  |- wi(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wb(wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2)))
} = {
  impbida(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2))
  sylan(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wbr(c1, cwdom, c0))
  3syl(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c0), wbr(c1, cen, c0), wbr(c1, cdom, c0))
  ensym(c0, c1)
  endom(c1, c0)
  domwdom(c1, c0)
  wdomtr(c1, c0, c2)
  sylan(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c1, cwdom, c2), wbr(c0, cwdom, c2), wbr(c0, cwdom, c1))
  syl(wbr(c0, cen, c1), wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(c0, cdom, c1))
  endom(c0, c1)
  domwdom(c0, c1)
  wdomtr(c0, c1, c2)
}

blocks.name: wdompwdom
blocks.content: Weak dominance strengthens to usual dominance on the power sets. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 11-Feb-2015.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 5-May-2015.)
blocks.origin:
thm wdompwdom(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)))
} = {
  pm2.61ine(c0, emptycls, wi(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1))))
  syl5ibr(wceq(c0, emptycls), wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)), wbr(cpw(emptycls), cdom, cpw(c1)))
  mpisyl(wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(cpw(emptycls), cdom, cpw(c1)), wcel(cpw(c1), universe), wss(cpw(emptycls), cpw(c1)))
  pwexd(c1, universe, wbr(c0, cwdom, c1))
  brrelex2i(c0, cwdom, c1)
  relwdom()
  mpbi(wss(cpw(emptycls), cpw(c1)), wss(emptycls, c1))
  0ss(c1)
  sspwb(emptycls, c1)
  ssdomg(cpw(c1), universe, cpw(emptycls))
  breq1d(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1), cpw(emptycls), wceq(c0, emptycls))
  pweq(c0, emptycls)
  syl6bi(wne(c0, emptycls), wbr(c0, cwdom, c1), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)), wex(hs0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0)))
  brwdomn0(hs0, c0, c1)
  exlimiv(hs0, wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)))
  mpan(wfo(cv(hs0), c1, c0), wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)), wcel(cv(hs0), universe))
  vex(hs0)
  fopwdom(cv(hs0), universe, c1, c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.w(wbr(cpw(c0), cdom, cpw(c1)))
}

blocks.name: canthwdom
blocks.content: Cantor's Theorem, stated using weak dominance (this is actually a stronger statement than ~ canth2 , equivalent to ~ canth ). (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 15-May-2015.)

blocks.name: wdomd
blocks.content: Deduce weak dominance from an implicit onto function. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 13-Feb-2015.)
blocks.origin:
thm wdomd(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wbr(c0, cwdom, c1))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, c2))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3)))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
  -| diffsw(s1, w0)
} = {
  wdom2d(s0, s1, c0, c1, universe, c2, c3, w0)
  ssexd(c0, cab(s0, wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3))), universe, w0)
  syl(w0, wcel(cab(s0, wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3))), universe), wcel(c1, c2))
  abrexexg(s0, s1, c1, c2, c3)
  sylibr(w0, wss(c0, cab(s0, wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3)))), wal(s0, wi(wcel(cv(s0), c0), wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3)))))
  alrimiv(s0, w0, wi(wcel(cv(s0), c0), wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3))))
  ex(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0), wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3)))
  ssab(s0, c0, wrex(s1, c1, wceq(cv(s0), c3)))
}

blocks.name: ixpiunwdom
blocks.content: Describe an onto function from the indexed cartesian product to the indexed union. Together with ~ ixpssmapg this shows that ` U_ x e. A B ` and ` X_ x e. A B ` have closely linked cardinalities. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 27-Aug-2015.)
blocks.origin:
thm ixpiunwdom(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  |- wi(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls)), wbr(ciun(s0, c0, c2), cwdom, cxp(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0)))
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
} = {
  syl2anc(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls)), wbr(ciun(s0, c0, c2), cwdom, cxp(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0)), wcel(cmpo(hs0, hs1, cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0, cfv(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), universe), wfo(cmpo(hs0, hs1, cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0, cfv(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), cxp(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0), ciun(s0, c0, c2)))
  syl3anc(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls)), wcel(cmpo(hs0, hs1, cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0, cfv(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), universe), wf(cmpo(hs0, hs1, cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0, cfv(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), cxp(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0), ciun(s0, c0, c2)), wcel(cxp(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0), universe), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3))
  xpexd(cixp(s0, c0, c2), c0, universe, c1, w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls)))
  syl(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls)), wcel(cixp(s0, c0, c2), universe), wss(cixp(s0, c0, c2), co(ciun(s0, c0, c2), cmap, c0)))
  3ad2ant2(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(ciun(s0, c0, c2), c3), wne(cixp(s0, c0, c2), emptycls), wss(cixp(s0, c0, c2), co(ciun(s0, c0, c2), cmap, c0)))

  ovex(ciun(s0, c0, c2), cmap, c0)
